---
import "../styles/global.css";
import { ClientRouter } from "astro:transitions";
import Icon from "../components/Icon.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>For Users</title>
    <ClientRouter />
  </head>
  <body class="h-screen flex flex-col" style="background-color: #f4f4f4;">
    <header class="flex justify-between px-6 py-4 items-center sticky top-0 z-10" style="background-color: #f4f4f4;">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <a href="/"><img src="/habitat-wordmark.svg" /></a>
      </div>
      <nav class="flex text-lg gap-8">
        <a href="/users">For users</a>
        <a href="/developers"><u>For developers</u></a>
      </nav>
      <div class="flex-1 flex justify-end gap-4 items-center">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/habitat-network/habitat"
          aria-label="GitHub"
        >
          <Icon name="github" class="w-6 h-6" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/habitat.network" aria-label="Bluesky">
          <Icon name="bluesky" class="w-6 h-6" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://habitat.leaflet.pub" aria-label="Leaflet">
          <Icon name="leaflet" class="w-6 h-6" />
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>
    <main class="flex flex-col items-center gap-16">
      <div class="prose mt-8">
        <h1>Usher in a new era of the web.</h1>
        <p>
          If you believe, like us, that the current status quo is broken, come
          help us do better. The web didn't become the way it is now because
          it's the only way -- it's because money and infrastructure was poured
          into making it so. We can redirect this energy towards building a web
          that doesn't require software companies to prey on users to survive.
          After all, it's just code.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose">
        <h3>
          Aligned incentives: you own the product, the user owns their data.
        </h3>
        <p>
          We believe software is at its best when company business models align
          with user incentives. Users should pay you because they want to stay,
          not because they can't leave.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose">
        <h3>No infrastructure necessary.</h3>
        <p>
          Today, every company has to rebuild some of the same infrastructure:
          user accounts, permissions, data sync. We get these primitives right
          so you can focus on what matters most: building the best user
          experiences. Save the time, money, and compute by building on habitat.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose">
        <h3>Trivial integration with other apps built on ATProtocol.</h3>
        <p>
          The benefit of an open data protocol is that products thrive together.
          You don't just read and write to your application's data silo;
          instead, shared data schemas allow for unlimited integration and
          cross-app interactions.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose py-12 px-8 w-[60vw] max-w-none">
        <h2>
          Get started by reading our docs here, and join the discussion on
          Bluesky/Blacksky/your favorite platform by tagging @habitat.network.
        </h2>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
